  <text xml:lang="ta" type="edition">
    <body>
      <div rend="parallel">
        <p xml:id="KT371-kilavi">varaiviṭai vaṟpuṟuttun tōḻikkut talaimakaḷ colliyatu. </p>


        <p xml:lang="en">Uttered by HER to the confidante, who encourages [her
          while waiting for] the time of marriage. </p>
      </div>

      <div rend="parallel">
        <lg xml:id="KT371">
          <l> kaivaḷai nekiḻtalu meypacap pūrtalu</l>
          <l> maipaṭu cilampi ṉaivaṉam vitti</l>
          <l> yaruviyiṉ viḷaikku nāṭaṉoṭu</l>
          <l> maruvēṉ ṟōḻiyatu kāmamō peritē.</l>


        </lg>

        <lg xml:lang="en">
          <l>Bangles [are] loosening on the hand and pallor creeping up on the body. <note place="foot">Line 1 might be read as an independent sentence, although the verbal nouns in <term xml:lang="ta"> -al </term>  seem to ask for some sort of finite complement. Cām. gives a different interpretation, taking  <term xml:lang="ta"> nekiḻtal </term> and   <term xml:lang="ta"> ūrtal </term> as direct objects to   <term xml:lang="ta"> maruvēṉ </term>. Problematic about this latter solution is that it requires taking the sociative  <term xml:lang="ta"> nāṭaṉoṭu </term> as a causal instrumental, which is at least unusual. This choice between two not so happy constructions considerably changes the message. In one case SHE does not want to get involved with <term xml:lang="ta"> kāmam </term>, since she knows about the consequences, in the other <term xml:lang="ta"> kāmam </term> helps her bear the time of waiting. </note>
          </l>
          <l rend="indent">With the man from a land, where they sow wild rice on the mountain side</l>
          <l rend="indent2">covered with collyrium [clouds <note place="foot"> Is <term xml:lang="ta">  mai </term> "collyrium" still a metaphor or already a word for "cloud"? (Cf. KT 319.4, 339.2).   </note>      and] let [it] ripen by the waterfall,</l>
          <l>I don't join together, friend.</l>
          <l rend="indent7">That desire? It [is] big.</l>

          <lg type="alternate">
            <l rend="indent">Into bangles loosening on the hand and pallor creeping up on the body,</l>
            <l rend="indent2">because of the man from a land, where they sow wild rice</l>
            <l rend="indent8">on the mountain side</l>
            <l rend="indent3">covered with collyrium [clouds and] lets [it] ripen by the waterfall,</l>
            <l>I won't get involved, friend.</l>
            <l rend="indent6">As for that desire, it is big.</l>
          </lg>

        </lg>
      </div>
    </body>
